<TITLE> Bridge collapse snaps Ctg-Sylhet road link </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, Mar 1 (bdnews24.com)  Road communications between Chittagong, Sylhet and Comilla were snapped on Monday after a bridge collapsed at Brahmanbaria, police said. Hundreds of vehicles remained stranded on both sides of the Panchabati bridge at Mohiuddinnagar since a part of the bridge caved in around 11am. Sergeant Md Bayezid at Brahmanbaria Sadar thana told bdnews24.com that the bridge broke down when a truck laden with corrugated sheet was crossing it. He said efforts are being made to remove the truck and the repair work will begin soon after. bdn
